# Repository root — solution scope

**What this file is:** The authoritative repo-root guide for where code and rules live—`frontend/` vs `*.svc/` (including `aspire.svc/`)—and which component owns each concern.

**When to use it:** Before adding features, APIs, persistence, UI, or rules anywhere in the monorepo; when choosing between `frontend/`, `aspire.svc/`, or a gRPC microservice; when looking up dev ports or per-service rule locations.

**How to use it:** Read **Format** and **Build**; apply every line in **Rules**; follow per-component rules via **Related** and the rule-pointer table—never duplicate Next.js or per-service stacks in root `.cursor/rules/`.

---

## Format

### Solution components

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| **Name** | Component name as used in docs and local dev |
| **Path** | Repo-relative root folder (from repository root) |
| **What it is** | One-line purpose and how it fits the solution |
| **When to use it** | When an agent should extend or call this component (vs another) |

| Name | Path | What it is | When to use it |
|------|------|------------|----------------|
| **Arb Aspire** | `aspire.svc/` | Next.js **app-composition host** (modular monolith): UI, `aspire.svc/lib/`, and bounded contexts under `aspire.svc/services/`. | Host-specific composition, aspire service registry, or legacy architect shell—not the primary product UI (`frontend/`). |
| **Arb Frontend** | `frontend/` | Primary **Next.js presentation** app: pages, components, and thin gRPC adapters only. | Any user-facing UI, routes, layout, or view models; never domain rules, authz, or persistence. |
| **IAM** | `iam.svc/` | **Identity and access**: authentication, authorization, RBAC over gRPC + DynamoDB. | Users, logins, roles, permissions, tokens, or security decisions shared across the platform. |
| **ARB Solutions** | `solutions.svc/` | **ARB solution domain**: solution capabilities and data under ARB architect ownership and team review. | Solution metadata, review workflow, or behavior specific to the ARB solution—not IAM, files, or generic UI. |
| **Storage** | `storage.svc/` | **File/object storage**: logical folders, presigned S3 URLs, and metadata over gRPC. | Uploads, downloads, blobs, or file references—not workflows, auth, or solution business rules. |
| **General AI Agent** | `general.ai.agent.svc/` | **Strands + Bedrock** conversational agent over gRPC (in-memory sessions per `conversation_id`). | AI chat, agent tools, or model-driven assistance—call from server-side code (`frontend/` / `aspire.svc/`), not browser gRPC. |
| **Notification** | `notification.svc/` | **Outbound notifications** (e.g. SNS email) over gRPC. | Email or event fan-out to users—not in-app UI state or domain persistence. |
| **Collaboration** | `collaboration.svc/` | **Aliases and discussions**: stable entity aliases and threaded messages over gRPC + DynamoDB. | Comments, threads, or human-readable aliases for platform entities—not duplicate comment storage in other services. |
| **Document storage** | `document-storage.svc/` | **Generic document storage**: group-scoped logical tables, item CRUD, vector search, attachments over gRPC + DynamoDB. | Structured documents, workbook rows, imports, or admin requirement-document UI—not solution review or generic file storage. |
| **Arch diagram agent** | `arch.diagram.agent.svc/` | **Diagram-to-graph conversion**: validates diagram input and runs Bedrock-backed conversion jobs over gRPC + DynamoDB. | Architecture diagram ingestion, instance-graph conversion, or conversion job lifecycle—not generic chat or document CRUD. |

